11. The English mode tends to make the Latin a LIVING LANGUAGE.

There is too much tendency now to make the ancient languages (lead languages, a kind of rare accomplish- ment, a kind of outside affair that has no real practical value. The new mode by its oddness and strangeness greatly increases this tendency.

The student hears foreign sounds constantly, sees the Latin divorced from all direct beneficial effect upon his claily vocabulary, and is consequently made to feel that his Latin is only a relic of a distant age. Nothing should bc encouraged by scholars that will make the ancient tongues appear less familiar, less practical‚ less vital than they are now.
